  "texts": [
    "Here, FLAN-T5 small and FLAN-T5 base demonstrate similar performance in terms of recall and accuracy, while the base model exhibits slightly better performance with precision and f1-scores of 0.78 and 0.79, respectively, which is a noticeable increase from the small variant, meaning it is more precise in its predictions.",
    "Nor-T5 small maintains comparable recall, precision, accuracy, and f1-scores of 0.77, indicating a balanced performance to predict positive instances correctly and to identify the most positive instances.Transitioning to full fine-tuning in Table 14, all models exhibit enhanced f1-scores, indicative of improved predictive relevance and balanced precision-recall, as compared to the performance of these models in Table 13.",
    "FLAN-T5 base records the highest precision increase to 0.82, an accuracy score of 0.83, and an f1-score of 0.80, indicating a balance between precision and recall and also suggesting that full fine-tuning significantly refines the model's predictive accuracy and overall performance.",
    "FLAN-T5 small also shows marginal gains in precision and f1-score, underscoring the benefits of a more extensive fine-tuning process.",
    "In the case of Nor-T5 small, it exhibits a slight improvement as compared to few-shot fine-tuning.Comparing the results of both these tables, it is evident that full fine-tuning combined with generative configurations yields improved model performance."
